ding a new perspective on our nation's current dilemmas, Smith also offers hope for change through an embrace of authentic history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCold WarxHistoriography. 0aNational characteristics, American. 0aSpanish-American War, 1898xHistoriography. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300195293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300195293.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles